Citation.sTitle: A study of densities and volumetric properties of binary mixtures of N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone with xylene at different temperatures and atmospheric pressure
Citation.sAbstract: The densities of binary mixtures of N-methyl-2-pyrrolidone (NMP) with o-xylene, m-xylene, and p-xylene, including those of pure liquids, over the entire composition range were measured at T = (293.15, 303.15, 313.15, 323.15, 333.15, 343.15, and 353.15) K and atmospheric pressure. From the experimental data, the excess molar volume, V E m, and partial molar volumes, Vm,1 and Vm,2, were calculated over whole composition range. The V E m values were found negative for all the mixtures at each temperature studied, and decrease with rising temperature. The extent of negative deviations in V E m values follows the order: p-xylene greater than m-xylene greater than o-xylene. The variation of these parameters with composition and temperature of the mixtures has been discussed.
